---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Ventures" description="Operating roles with real stake — not advisory, not passive.">
  <main class="max-w-prose mx-auto px-5 py-12">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-sm font-mono text-fg-muted mb-2">operating</p>
      <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-4xl mb-3">Ventures</h1>
      <p class="text-fg-secondary">Business affiliations with real stake. Not advisory, not passive.</p>
    </header>

    <article class="border border-border rounded-lg p-5 mb-4">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2 gap-4">
        <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-lg">
          <a href="https://dwtrimco.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:text-green transition-colors">DW Trim</a>
        </h2>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-fg-muted whitespace-nowrap">Managing Partner</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-fg-secondary text-sm mb-3">
        Carpentry company — a one-man operation that's scaled up and down for years. I'm joining as Managing Partner to help scale past the greater Tampa Bay area.
      </p>
      <p class="text-fg-secondary text-sm mb-3">
        The principal craftsman owns the trade; I own the backend — operations, tech leverage, the scaling playbook. We're explicit about who's the senior in the craft and who's the senior in growth.
      </p>
      <p class="text-fg-secondary text-sm">
        Strategic bet: prove the scaling playbook on a real craft business with proven product and existing customer base, then springboard follow-on ventures.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
